This paper is primarily focused on the performance and behavior of deep neural networks (DNNs) in classification tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the ability of DNNs to generalize and memorize data, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses image classification as an example, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of classic classifiers such as $k$-nearest neighbors, support vector machines, and logistic regression also suggests a connection to neural networks and their applications in computational neuroscience (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
